## Extraction Requirements

Extract ALL of the following entity types present in the document:

### Medications
For each medication, extract:
- drug_name (required)
- dosage (e.g. "500mg")
- frequency (e.g. "twice daily")
- route (e.g. "oral")
- prescribing_physician
- prescription_date

### Diagnoses
For each diagnosis, extract:
- condition_name (required)
- icd_code (if present)
- diagnosis_date
- treating_provider
- status (active / resolved / chronic)

### Procedures
For each procedure, extract:
- procedure_name (required)
- procedure_date
- performing_physician
- facility
- cpt_code (if present)

### Allergies
For each allergy, extract:
- allergen (required)
- reaction_type (e.g. "anaphylaxis", "rash")
- severity (mild / moderate / severe / life-threatening)
- onset_date
- status (active / inactive)

## Attribution Requirements (MANDATORY)
Every extracted item MUST include:
- page_number: integer (use 1 if single-page or unknown)
- extraction_region: brief description of where on the page the value was found
  (e.g. "top-right header", "medication table row 3", "allergy section")
- confidence: your confidence score for THIS specific item in the range 0.0–1.0
  - 0.95–1.00: value is clearly and unambiguously stated in the document
  - 0.80–0.94: value is stated but may need minor interpretation
  - 0.60–0.79: value is partially stated or inferred — will require staff review
  - 0.00–0.59: value is guessed or ambiguous — will require staff review
  - null: use ONLY when you genuinely cannot assess extraction quality

Items with confidence below 0.80 or null will be flagged for mandatory staff review.
Do NOT omit the confidence field — set it to null if unsure rather than leaving it out.

